About the university

~ €613 / year

Programs in demand Specialized university International cooperation

The ENS is a superior institution for studies centered on education. It has 14 teaching departments. It confers national diplomas (DIPES 1, DIPES 2, DIP, CO and DIPEN). In the various administrative departments, it houses a wax, a restaurant and sports equipment. For optimal research, the campus is irrigated by free wifi access to students and teachers. Through its selective recruitment, it is one of the best training schools in Cameroon. This state of affairs is reflected in the employment of ENS graduates in all sectors related to the development of the country.

Required documents for admission

When applying for admission to École Normale Supérieure in Gabon you should prepare all required documents. Request a list of necessary documents directly from a university, as it may vary for different countries. Using our live chat, you can also ask for sample documents.

Free Apply is not responsible for the content of this page. Through the Site, Free Apply provides an online catalog which you can use to find different types of educational institutions. It’s possible for a new university to be registered by any user, however only verified university representatives will be able to manage, reply in chat and make changes to a university page. Once the University registers its official representative, it has the right to block access for others to edit the information. Further control over the content will be carried out by the representative of the University. Registration with the Free-Apply.com catalog is free.
